    {
      "hash": "f973471",
      "message": "fix: add error handling to session route + show error UI instead of infinite spinner\n\n- Wrap /api/session/me in try/catch, log errors, return 500 with detail\n- Check DATABASE_URL is set before querying\n- Add force-dynamic export to prevent static rendering\n- Restore uuid and is_primary_owner fields in SQL queries\n- SessionProvider now shows error message + retry button instead of\n  spinning forever when session fetch fails\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "neil",
      "date": "2026-03-16"
    },
    {
      "hash": "53fb5c5",
      "message": "fix: bust service worker cache and scope caching to PWA routes only\n\nThe SW was caching all GET responses including JS bundles, causing\nstale code to be served even after Vercel deploys. Now only caches\nPWA shell, manifest, and static assets.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "neil",
      "date": "2026-03-16"
    },
    {
      "hash": "22d5f0b",
      "message": "feat: edit item modal + fix session auth to use local API route\n\n- Add EditItemModal with station selector, quantity +/-, notes, mods link\n- Wire edit button in PhoneOrderEntry and TabletOrderEntry to open modal\n- Remove SUSHI course badge — sushi items show as APP or ENTREE\n- Rewrite useAppAuth to call /api/session/me instead of external backend\n- No longer depends on NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL for session initialization\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "neil",
      "date": "2026-03-16"
    },
